trans-unit.source: Levels are the foundation of approvals setup. For an effective approval rule, first you need to define approval levels, then combine one or multiple levels into approval policy and finally assign policy to a particular business function. Approval policy is a configurable entity of request management that helps associate various request types with approval processes defined in the request service only for request-level and operation-level approvals. It associates approval workflows to be initiated at request or operation levels for a request type.
trans-unit.target: Levels are the foundation of approvals setup. For an effective approval rule, first you need to define approval levels, then combine one or multiple levels into approval policy and finally assign policy to a particular business function. Approval policy is a configurable entity of request management that helps associate various request types with approval processes defined in the request service only for request-level and operation-level approvals. It associates approval workflows to be initiated at request or operation levels for a request type.
trans-unit.note: Approval levels how to use description

trans-unit.source: You can define multiple approval policies for a request type. Each approval policy is associated with an approval process. When the request is submitted, in the approval initiation phase, all the approval processes associated with the request type are picked up dynamically. Each approval policy has a priority in the backend. Each approval policy decides on what process to invoke based on approval policy priority and approval policy rule.
trans-unit.target: You can define multiple approval policies for a request type. Each approval policy is associated with an approval process. When the request is submitted, in the approval initiation phase, all the approval processes associated with the request type are picked up dynamically. trans-unit.source: Service agreement is A contract that includes one or more legal entities. A legal entity that is participating in a service agreement can allow a subset of its users to act through that service agreement and/or allow a subset of its arrangements to be accessed through the service agreement. Within each service agreement, permissions to perform specific tasks are granted to users, including access to arrangements shared by one or more legal entities participating in that service agreement. The permissions, or privileges, are assigned to a user through a job role. A service agreement may have a time limit. It is also possible to disable a SA. Permissions granted to users in the not started, expired, or disabled Service Agreement are not active. It is possible to assign users that are added to the Service Agreement as service agreement Admins so that they can instantly perform tasks like managing users and permissions with the permissions defined in a special type of job role as well known as a System Job Role. Service Agreements can be defined as either Retail or Business categories same way as legal entities within service agreements.
trans-unit.target: Service agreement is A contract that includes one or more legal entities. A legal entity that is participating in a service agreement can allow a subset of its users to act through that service agreement and/or allow a subset of its arrangements to be accessed through the service agreement. Within each service agreement, permissions to perform specific tasks are granted to users, including access to arrangements shared by one or more legal entities participating in that service agreement. The permissions, or privileges, are assigned to a user through a job role. A service agreement may have a time limit. It is also possible to disable a SA. Permissions granted to users in the not started, expired, or disabled Service Agreement are not active. It is possible to assign users that are added to the Service Agreement as service agreement Admins so that they can instantly perform tasks like managing users and permissions with the permissions defined in a special type of job role as well known as a System Job Role. Service Agreements can be defined as either Retail or Business categories same way as legal entities within service agreements.

trans-unit.note: What is Single service agreement title

trans-unit.source: A special kind of service agreement is called the single service agreement, which has the following characteristics: Has one legal entity participant and, once configured, the participant cannot be changed. A legal entity that is participating in a single service agreement allows all of its users to act through that service agreement and also allows all of its arrangements to be accessed through the service agreement. All users of a corresponding legal entity are added to a single agreement by default and can not be assigned or removed explicitly. Once the user is granted some administrative permissions, such as managing account groups, they have the power to execute the task in any service agreement lower in the hierarchy. For example, if a bank employee is assigned the manage account groups permission in the bank’s single service agreement, the user can manage account groups in any service agreement lower in the hierarchy.
trans-unit.target: A special kind of service agreement is called the single service agreement, which has the following characteristics: Has one legal entity participant and, once configured, the participant cannot be changed. A legal entity that is participating in a single service agreement allows all of its users to act through that service agreement and also allows all of its arrangements to be accessed through the service agreement. All users of a corresponding legal entity are added to a single agreement by default and can not be assigned or removed explicitly. Once the user is granted some administrative permissions, such as managing account groups, they have the power to execute the task in any service agreement lower in the hierarchy.
